@c @section Linux

@c If you want Emacs to load the file 'oef-mode.el' when it starts, put the file 'oef-mode.el'
@c in the dir "~/.emacs.d/lisp/", (create that directory if it doesn't exist).
@c By convention, the dir ~/.emacs.d/lisp/ is for packages you manually installed.
@c Then put the following in your Emacs init file "~/.emacs"
@c vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvv
@c  (add-to-list 'load-path "~/.emacs.d/lisp/") ;; Tell Emacs where is your personal elisp lib dir
@c  (load "oef") ;; load the packaged named oef (best not to include the ending “.el” or “.elc”)
@c ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
@c before the line (package-initialize).




